The article announces that June is African-American Music Appreciation Month in the United States. It acknowledges the significant contributions of African-American composers, singers, songwriters, and musicians to the nation's culture. The article highlights how African-American music has evolved throughout history, from spirituals and gospel to blues, jazz, soul, and rock and roll. It also mentions the impact of African-American composers in traditional genres such as musical theater, opera, classical symphony, and choral music. The proclamation calls upon public officials, educators, and the general public to observe the month with activities and programs that raise awareness and foster appreciation of music composed, arranged, and performed by African Americans.